From: HyprWM Fedora maintainers
Subject: [PATCH] cmake: use GNU installation directories

Bare install(TARGETS) calls otherwise default to /usr/lib on 64-bit Fedora.
Load GNUInstallDirs so plugin libraries follow the configured architecture
libdir before the RPM moves them into Hyprland's private plugin directory.

--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -4,6 +4,8 @@ project(hyprland-plugins
     LANGUAGES CXX
 )
 
+include(GNUInstallDirs)
+
 set(CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD 23)
 set(CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD_REQUIRED ON)
